From Bob Blackshaw Subject Re Damn Ferigner's Be Taken Over In Peter Nelson writes In article cos Bob Blackshaw writes In C Peter Nelson writes Norway where you appear to be posting from is just such a place although it has always escaped my understanding just what the appeal to allegedly rational people of such a scheme might What gives King Olav V or whoever it is now my atlas is from the right to any special legal status or title based on a mere accident of birth To begin with it's quite inexpensive compared to here what with our having six former presidents still alive drawing pensions expense accounts and secret service Maybe so but they were after all In the corporate world it's SOP for retiring senior executives to be given nice pensions The point is that they performed a service and this is part of the compensation The only service royals have to perform for their free ride is being We might be better off had some of our former presidents done peter PS which is not to say that some of our presidents have not provided a service for the country too dissimilar from what occurs when a bull services a cow for those of you familiar with cattle breeding